<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-dzNzwvRIO_AGSay3hctuEA" name="new_task,_p3_xQFOUEeCU6fknDNFamA" guid="-dzNzwvRIO_AGSay3hctuEA" changeDate="2011-06-27T00:17:52.796-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The CM Plan is a composite document which contains all the information necessary to effectively carry out configuration&#xD;
    management tasks for the project. This includes the documentation of&amp;nbsp;CM policies and procedures.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.mgmt.configuration_mgmt.base-ibm/workproducts/configuration_management_plan_F3F7F5C3.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_Sfx6kFPJEeC0QeFAXej8ZA&quot;>Configuration Management Plan&lt;/a> describes the necessary input for effective CM&#xD;
    planning. The template is intended to serve as a guideline and intent of each section should be addressed within the&#xD;
    context of a given project/product.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task is part of tailoring a process for a project ( See &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.mgmt.project_process_tailoring.base/tasks/tailor_process_5C4EB327.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_NOBsuCZLEd-QuZFPf_YdqQ&quot;>Tailor the Process&lt;/a>)&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_VTIZwI2iEeCWFd_rKFT43w" name="Identify and Document CM Policies and Procedures" guid="_VTIZwI2iEeCWFd_rKFT43w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
 class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
    Policies may include&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
         class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            Identification Policies to identify configuration items and related components that will be placed under&#xD;
            configuration management.&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
         class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            Naming Policies to&amp;nbsp;identify configuration items . This also includes naming policies&amp;nbsp;of promoted&#xD;
            baselines.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
         class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            Baselining Policies&amp;nbsp;for baselining configuration items.&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
         class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            Archiving Policies to ensure that project software and related assets (master documents) are backed-up,&#xD;
            cataloged and transferred to designated storage sites.&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
         class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            Configuration Status Reporting Policies&amp;nbsp;determine how often a configuration audit is required and&#xD;
            designate where configuration items must be&amp;nbsp;stored as well as what actions must be performed when there is&#xD;
            a change to configuration items.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
 class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'&quot;>The configuration management procedures help the project to document&#xD;
    configuration management activities that are to be planned, implemented controlled and organized.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br&#xD;
style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
 class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
 class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
    Configuration Procedure may include&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
         class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            Naming Procedures&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
         class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            Change and Control Management Procedures&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-AUTOSPACE: ideograph-numeric; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-layout-grid-align: auto; punctuation-wrap: hanging; mso-vertical-align-alt: auto&quot;&#xD;
         class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            Promote baseline procedures,&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_j1s1sFVXEeC0QeFAXej8ZA" name="Review and Approve the CM Plan   " guid="_j1s1sFVXEeC0QeFAXej8ZA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    During the review, the attendees review the configuration management (CM) plan which is developed. Using the&#xD;
    established&amp;nbsp;CM&amp;nbsp;policies, the group determines if CM plan is developed accurately.The project manager decides&#xD;
    whether to approve CM plan or not.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_j3V0cFVXEeC0QeFAXej8ZA" name="Maintain the CM Plan  " guid="_j3V0cFVXEeC0QeFAXej8ZA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Re-visit the CM plan throughout the lifecycle to ensure that the overall CM strategy is still relevant to how the&#xD;
    project is being developed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Project CM Plan itself needs to be placed under configuration control and should be checked into the source&#xD;
    control.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>The purpose of this task is to describe all CM related tasks to be performed during the course of the product/project&#xD;
lifecycle and document how product related CM tasks are to be planned, implemented controlled and organized.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
